o-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zge1665702663349.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zge1665702663349.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zge1665702663349.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zge1665702663349\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Uniface Database I/O\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zge1665702663349__uniface_database_i_o_134889\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface allows you to access data in multiple DBMSs in a uniform way, simultaneously. The term DBMS is used generically here to describe any structured form of data storage that Uniface understands. According to this definition, a record management system is also a DBMS. All the actions carried out on database tables or files occur via the DBMS interface.\n </p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"zge1665702663349__fig_d43490e1_d43491e1_d43492e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>DBMS Interface</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"DBMS Interface communicates with DBMS connectors\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/iointerfaces.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43496e1_d43497e1_d43498e1\">The DBMS interface comprises a standard set of calls that handle every action you want to carry out. For example, the DBMS interface generates a select call when a user tries to retrieve data from the database and a write call for inserting data into the database.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zge1665702663349__topic_d27987e1_d27988e1_d27989e1_d27990e1_d27991e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d117237e66\">\n            \n DML and DDL\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43502e1_d43503e1_d43504e1\">The DBMS interface accesses a DBMS via a DBMS connector, which translates the Uniface calls into the Data Definition Language (DDL) or Data Manipulation Language (DML) of whichever DBMS you are using.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43505e1_d43506e1_d43507e1\">For example, a user can retrieve data from a database by clicking a button that invokes the ^RETRIEVE structure editor function. This initiates the following sequence of events:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zge1665702663349__li_d21752e1_d21753e1_d21754e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43508e1_d43509e1_d43510e1\">The ^RETRIEVE function activates the retrieve trigger ProcScript module for the component.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zge1665702663349__li_d21755e1_d21756e1_d21757e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43511e1_d43512e1_d43513e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve</span> ProcScript\n                  statement in the &lt;Retrieve&gt; trigger activates the read trigger for every\n                  entity in the component.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zge1665702663349__li_d21758e1_d21759e1_d21760e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43514e1_d43515e1_d43516e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read</span> ProcScript statement\n                  in the read trigger of each entity causes the DBMS interface to issue the S\n                  (Select) call to the DBMS connector in the path, for each retrieved occurrence of\n                  each entity.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zge1665702663349__li_d21761e1_d21762e1_d21763e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43517e1_d43518e1_d43519e1\">The DBMS connector selects the required data from the database using the correct DML.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zge1665702663349__p_d43520e1_d43521e1_d43522e1\">Provided you do not use DBMS-specific functionality such as SQL code (with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript instruction), you can port your Uniface application to drive many different DBMSs without recoding. The calls from Uniface always remain the same, although the implementation can differ between DBMSs.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Database I/O Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Database I/O Uniface allows you to access data in multiple DBMSs in a uniform way, simultaneously. The term DBMS is used generically here to describe any structured form of data storage that Uniface understands. According to this definition, a record management system is also a DBMS. All the actions carried out on database tables or files occur via the DBMS interface. Figure 1. DBMS Interface The DBMS interface comprises a standard set of calls that handle every action you want to carry out. For example, the DBMS interface generates a select call when a user tries to retrieve data from the database and a write call for inserting data into the database. DML and DDL The DBMS interface accesses a DBMS via a DBMS connector, which translates the Uniface calls into the Data Definition Language (DDL) or Data Manipulation Language (DML) of whichever DBMS you are using. For example, a user can retrieve data from a database by clicking a button that invokes the ^RETRIEVE structure editor function. This initiates the following sequence of events: The ^RETRIEVE function activates the retrieve trigger ProcScript module for the component. The retrieve ProcScript statement in the <Retrieve> trigger activates the read trigger for every entity in the component. The read ProcScript statement in the read trigger of each entity causes the DBMS interface to issue the S (Select) call to the DBMS connector in the path, for each retrieved occurrence of each entity. The DBMS connector selects the required data from the database using the correct DML. Provided you do not use DBMS-specific functionality such as SQL code (with the sql ProcScript instruction), you can port your Uniface application to drive many different DBMSs without recoding. The calls from Uniface always remain the same, although the implementation can differ between DBMSs. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}